Ingest_LDD.name: Voyager Mission Namespace Dictionary
Ingest_LDD.comment: v1.0.0.0 2022-05-04 Created by unifying the vg1 and vg2 namespace dictionaries, which will be deprecated. Specifically, the new base class Voyager contains elements common to both Voyager 1 and Voyager 2, and also contains exactly one of either the Voyager1 class or the Voyager2 class. The latter respectively contain elements relevant to only one of the two spacecraft. Also added new attributes and classes (TBD).

DD_Attribute.name: VICAR1_legacy_label
DD_Attribute.definition: The now-obsolete "VICAR-1" label that was originally attached to the image. To the extent possible, the information is captured in normal VICAR-2 and PDS4 labels. The labels are being retained for historical documentation purposes, and in case there is any question about how the rest of the label items were derived. Contemporaneous Voyager documentation sometimes refers to these legacy labels.

DD_Attribute.name: compression_state
DD_Attribute.definition: Whether the image compression mode was operating.

DD_Attribute.name: dsn_station_name
DD_Attribute.definition: Name of the DSN station where the image was received

DD_Attribute.name: dsn_station_number
DD_Attribute.definition: Numeric ID of DSN station where the image was received

DD_Attribute.name: edit_mode_id
DD_Attribute.definition: Edit mode of the camera. Original label parameter: EDIT MODE

DD_Attribute.name: edr_file_number
DD_Attribute.definition: File number within the tape where the image was originally stored

DD_Attribute.name: edr_tape_id
DD_Attribute.definition: Tape ID on which the image was originally stored

DD_Attribute.name: gain_mode_id
DD_Attribute.definition: The gain state of an instrument. Gain is a constant value, set by the observer, that indicates the approximate number of photon-excited electrons registered by the detector that correlate to one "data number" (DN). Original label parameter: GAIN

DD_Permissible_Value.value_meaning: The lower of the two gain states for Voyager ISS
The higher of the two gain states for Voyager ISS

DD_Attribute.name: lsb_truncate
DD_Attribute.definition: Whether the LSB Truncation mode was operating. In this mode, only a certain number of the least significant bits are kept, while the bits corresponding to larger place values are truncated.

DD_Permissible_Value.value_meaning: The LSB Truncate mode was off
The LSB Truncate mode was on

DD_Attribute.name: scan_mode_id
DD_Attribute.definition: Scan mode of the camera. Original label parameter: SCAN RATE

DD_Attribute.name: shutter_mode_id
DD_Attribute.definition: Shutter mode. Indicates which camera was shuttered, Narrow Angle and/or Wide Angle.

DD_Permissible_Value.value_meaning: Neither the Narrow Angle nor the Wide Angle shutter opened
Both the Narrow Angle and the Wide Angle shutters opened simultaneously

DD_Attribute.name: signal_to_noise_ratio
DD_Attribute.definition: Signal-to-noise ratio as measured by the camera onboard. Original label parameter: SNR

DD_Attribute.name: spacecraft_clock_start_count
DD_Attribute.definition: The spacecraft clock value at the beginning of a time period of interest.

DD_Attribute.name: spacecraft_clock_stop_count
DD_Attribute.definition: The spacecraft clock value at the end of a time period of interest.

DD_Attribute.name: telemetry_mode
DD_Attribute.definition: The mode within the Voyager ISS instrument of telemetry between the detector and the tape recorder.

DD_Permissible_Value.value_meaning: This keyword had no value in the original label. Meaning unclear.

DD_Attribute.name: vg1_mission_phase_name
DD_Attribute.definition: Time period within the Voyager 1 mission, as defined by the mission team.

DD_Permissible_Value.value_meaning: Voyager 1 Cruise between Earth and Jupiter: 1977-09-05 to 1979-01-06
Voyager 1 Cruise between Jupiter and Saturn: 1979-04-13 to 1980-08-22
Voyager 1 Interstellar Cruise: 1980-12-14 to End of Mission

DD_Attribute.name: vg2_mission_phase_name
DD_Attribute.definition: Time period within the Voyager 2 mission, as defined by the mission team.

DD_Permissible_Value.value_meaning: Voyager 2 Cruise between Earth and Jupiter: 1977-08-20 to 1979-04-25
Voyager 2 Cruise between Jupiter and Saturn: 1979-08-05 to 1981-06-05
Voyager 2 Cruise between Saturn and Uranus: 1981-09-25 to 1985-11-04
Voyager 2 Cruise between Uranus and Neptune: 1986-02-25 to 1989-06-05
Voyager 2 Interstellar Cruise: 1989-10-02 to End of Mission

DD_Class.name: Voyager
DD_Class.definition: This is the umbrella class for the Voyager mission dictionary.

DD_Class.name: Voyager1
DD_Class.definition: Container for elements relevant to Voyager 1.

DD_Class.name: Voyager2
DD_Class.definition: Container for elements relevant to Voyager 2.

DD_Class.name: ISS_Attributes
DD_Class.definition: Container for elements relevant to the Voyager ISS instrument and its observations.

DD_Class.name: ISS_Image_State
DD_Class.definition: Image state attributes relevant to the Voyager ISS instrument and its observations.

DD_Class.name: ISS_Instrument_State
DD_Class.definition: Instrument state attributes relevant to the Voyager ISS instrument and its observations.

DD_Class.name: Voyager_Telemetry
DD_Class.definition: Container for elements describing the process of transferring Voyager data from the spacecraft to Earth.
